0ad1535a-e11f-459d-8e8b-bca0f5132397.do_description: To make the output, you have to...draw a blue border around the red pixels. Fill in each pixel around the red pixel with blue. If the red pixel is near the border of the grid, fill in the pixels around it against the border.
0ad1535a-e11f-459d-8e8b-bca0f5132397.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same as input.
0ad1535a-e11f-459d-8e8b-bca0f5132397.see_description: In the input, you should see...a black grid with several colored pixels.

630115ab-c716-4e1a-9415-93f9a5b19e97.do_description: To make the output, you have to... draw a blue border around each red square (so it will look like a 3x3 blue square with a red square in the center), but if the red square is in the corner, just fill in 3 blue blocks around it.
630115ab-c716-4e1a-9415-93f9a5b19e97.grid_description: The output grid size... will be the same size as the input grid.
630115ab-c716-4e1a-9415-93f9a5b19e97.see_description: In the input, you should see... two red squares, and a few other colored squares.

66c25477-26b2-4d74-a818-d8afb2ce4a83.do_description: To make the output, you have to...surround only the red squares with a blue border that is one square wide.
66c25477-26b2-4d74-a818-d8afb2ce4a83.grid_description: The output grid size...remains the same.
66c25477-26b2-4d74-a818-d8afb2ce4a83.see_description: In the input, you should see...a series of colored boxes on a black background.
